                  <summary>It looks like a patchwork, but it isn't; the right hand line beginnings form the body of the original letter, the lines at the left form the end of the letter written along the left margin; there the 3rd line gives "greetings to you"</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Margins: Left</note>
                     <note type="general">Recto: 12 lines along the fibers at the right margin, then 5 lines running along the left margin of the letter against the fibers. Verso is possibly an address.</note>
